def get_tokens_up_to_path_start( tokens: list[str], include_start_coord: bool = True, tokenization_mode: TokenizationMode = <TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform: 'AOTP_UT_uniform'>) -> list[str]:
View on GitHub 
107def get_tokens_up_to_path_start(
108    tokens: list[str],
109    include_start_coord: bool = True,
110    tokenization_mode: TokenizationMode = TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
111) -> list[str]:
112    warnings.warn(
113        "`maze_tokenizer.get_tokens_up_to_path_start` will be deprecated for a `MazeTokenizerModular`-compatible function in a future release.",
114        TokenizerPendingDeprecationWarning,
115    )
116    path_start_idx: int = tokens.index(SPECIAL_TOKENS.PATH_START) + 1
117    if include_start_coord:
118        if is_UT(tokenization_mode):
119            return tokens[: path_start_idx + 1]
120        elif tokenization_mode == TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed:
121            return tokens[: path_start_idx + 5]
122        else:
123            raise ValueError(f"Invalid tokenization mode: {tokenization_mode}")
124    else:
125        return tokens[:path_start_idx]
@serializable_dataclass(properties_to_serialize=_MAZETOKENIZER_PROPERTIES_TO_SERIALIZE, kw_only=True)
class MazeTokenizer(muutils.json_serialize.serializable_dataclass.SerializableDataclass):
View on GitHub 
138@serializable_dataclass(
139    properties_to_serialize=_MAZETOKENIZER_PROPERTIES_TO_SERIALIZE, kw_only=True
140)
141class MazeTokenizer(SerializableDataclass):
142    """LEGACY Tokenizer for mazes
143
144    > [!CAUTION]
145    > `MazeTokenizerModular` is the new standard for tokenization. This class is no longer recommended
146    > for use, but will remain for compatibility with existing code.
147
148    # Parameters:
149     - `tokenization_mode: TokenizationMode`
150        mode of tokenization. required.
151    - `max_grid_size: int | None`
152        maximum grid size. required for actually turning text tokens to numerical tokens, but not for moving between coordinates/mazes and text
153
154    # Properties
155    - `name: str`
156        auto-generated name of the tokenizer from mode and size
157
158    ## Conditional Properties
159
160    - `node_strings_map: Mapping[CoordTup, str]`
161        map from node to string. This returns a `muutils.kappa.Kappa` object which you can use like a dictionary. returns `None` if not a `UT` mode
162
163    these all return `None` if `max_grid_size` is `None`.
164    Prepend `_` to the name to get a guaranteed type, and cause an exception if `max_grid_size` is `None`
165
166    - `token_arr: list[str]`
167        list of tokens, in order of their indices in the vocabulary
168    - `tokenizer_map: Mapping[str, int]`
169        map from token to index
170    - `vocab_size: int`
171        size of the vocabulary
172    - `padding_token_index: int`
173        index of the padding token
174
175    # Methods
176    - `coords_to_strings(coords: list[CoordTup]) -> list[str]`
177        convert a list of coordinates to a list of tokens. Optionally except, skip, or ignore non-coordinates
178    - `strings_to_coords(strings: list[str]) -> list[CoordTup]`
179        convert a list of tokens to a list of coordinates. Optionally except, skip, or ignore non-coordinates
180
181    """
182
183    # parameters
184    # ============================================================
185
186    tokenization_mode: TokenizationMode = serializable_field(
187        default=TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
188        serialization_fn=lambda x: x.value,
189        loading_fn=lambda x: TokenizationMode[x["tokenization_mode"]],
190    )
191
192    max_grid_size: int | None = serializable_field(default=None)
193
194    # properties
195    # ============================================================
196
197    @property
198    def name(self) -> str:
199        max_grid_size_str: str = (
200            f"-g{self.max_grid_size}" if self.max_grid_size is not None else ""
201        )
202        return f"maze_tokenizer-{self.tokenization_mode.value}{max_grid_size_str}"
203
204    @cached_property
205    def _node_strings_map(self) -> Mapping[CoordTup, list[str]]:
206        """map a coordinate to a token"""
207        if self.tokenization_mode in (
208            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
209            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
210        ):
211            return Kappa(_coord_to_strings_UT)
212        elif self.tokenization_mode == TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed:
213            return Kappa(_coord_to_strings_indexed)
214        else:
215            raise ValueError(
216                f"Invalid tokenization mode {self.tokenization_mode}",
217                f"expected one of {TokenizationMode.__members__}",
218            )
219
220    @cached_property
221    def node_strings_map(self) -> Mapping[CoordTup, list[str]] | None:
222        """map a coordinate to a token"""
223        if self.tokenization_mode in (
224            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
225            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
226        ):
227            return None
228        else:
229            return self._node_strings_map
230
231    # conditional properties (on max_grid_size existing)
232    # ------------------------------------------------------------
233
234    @cached_property
235    def _token_arr(self) -> list[str]:
236        """map from index to token"""
237        if self.max_grid_size is None:
238            raise ValueError(
239                f"max_grid_size must be specified to use token_arr property: {self.max_grid_size = }"
240            )
241
242        output: list[str] = list(SPECIAL_TOKENS.values())
243
244        if self.tokenization_mode in (
245            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
246            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
247        ):
248            output.extend(
249                [
250                    self._node_strings_map[coord][0]
251                    for coord in _NDINDEX_FUNC_MAP[self.tokenization_mode](
252                        self.max_grid_size
253                    )
254                ]
255            )
256        elif self.tokenization_mode == TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed:
257            # TODO: this is hacky, but we don't want to modify the original SPECIAL_TOKENS since that will break old models
258            output.extend(
259                [
260                    "(",
261                    ",",
262                    ")",  # new special chars
263                    *map(str, range(self.max_grid_size)),  # numbers
264                ]
265            )
266        else:
267            raise ValueError(
268                f"Invalid tokenization mode {self.tokenization_mode}",
269                f"expected one of {TokenizationMode.__members__}",
270            )
271
272        return output
273
274    @cached_property
275    def token_arr(self) -> list[str] | None:
276        if self.max_grid_size is None:
277            return None
278        return self._token_arr
279
280    @cached_property
281    def _tokenizer_map(self) -> dict[str, int]:
282        """map from token to index"""
283        return {token: i for i, token in enumerate(self._token_arr)}
284
285    @cached_property
286    def tokenizer_map(self) -> dict[str, int] | None:
287        if self.max_grid_size is None:
288            return None
289        return self._tokenizer_map
290
291    @property
292    def _vocab_size(self) -> int:
293        return len(self._token_arr)
294
295    @property
296    def vocab_size(self) -> int | None:
297        if self.max_grid_size is None:
298            return None
299        return self._vocab_size
300
301    @property
302    def _n_tokens(self) -> int:
303        # TODO: deprecate
304        return self._vocab_size
305
306    @property
307    def n_tokens(self) -> int | None:
308        if self.max_grid_size is None:
309            return None
310        return self._n_tokens
311
312    @cached_property
313    def _padding_token_index(self) -> int:
314        return self.tokenizer_map[SPECIAL_TOKENS.PADDING]
315
316    @cached_property
317    def padding_token_index(self) -> int | None:
318        if self.max_grid_size is None:
319            return None
320        return self._padding_token_index
321
322    # conversion functions
323    # ============================================================
324
325    def coords_to_strings(
326        self,
327        coords: list[CoordTup],
328        when_noncoord: WhenMissing = "skip",
329    ) -> list[str]:
330        if self.tokenization_mode in (
331            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
332            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
333        ):
334            return coords_to_strings(
335                coords=coords,
336                coord_to_strings_func=_coord_to_strings_UT,
337                when_noncoord=when_noncoord,
338            )
339        elif self.tokenization_mode == TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed:
340            return coords_to_strings(
341                coords=coords,
342                coord_to_strings_func=_coord_to_strings_indexed,
343                when_noncoord=when_noncoord,
344            )
345        else:
346            raise ValueError(
347                f"Invalid tokenization mode {self.tokenization_mode}",
348                f"expected one of {TokenizationMode.__members__}",
349            )
350
351    @staticmethod
352    def strings_to_coords(
353        text: str,
354        when_noncoord: WhenMissing = "skip",
355    ) -> list[str | CoordTup]:
356        return strings_to_coords(text=text, when_noncoord=when_noncoord)
357
358    def encode(self, text: str | list[str]) -> list[int]:
359        """encode a string or list of strings into a list of tokens"""
360        try:
361            if isinstance(text, str):
362                text = text.split()
363            return [self.tokenizer_map[token] for token in text]
364        except KeyError as e:
365            raise TokenError(
366                f"Token {e} not found",
367                f"in vocabulary of {self}:",
368                f"{self.token_arr}",
369            ) from e
370
371    def decode(
372        self, tokens: Sequence[int], joined_tokens: bool = False
373    ) -> list[str] | str:
374        """decode a list of tokens into a string or list of strings"""
375        try:
376            output: list[str] = [self.token_arr[token] for token in tokens]
377        except IndexError as e:
378            raise TokenError(
379                f"Token index '{e}' not found in vocabulary of length {self.vocab_size}"
380            ) from e
381        if joined_tokens:
382            return " ".join(output)
383        else:
384            return output
385
386    # UT-only coordinate stuff
387    # ============================================================
388
389    @cached_property
390    def coordinate_tokens_coords(self) -> dict[CoordTup, int]:
391        print(f"{self.tokenization_mode = }")
392        if not self.is_UT():
393            raise ValueError(
394                f"coordinate_tokens_coords is only valid for UT tokenization modes, got {self.tokenization_mode = }"
395            )
396        if self.max_grid_size is None:
397            raise ValueError(
398                f"max_grid_size must be specified to use coordinate_tokens: {self.max_grid_size = }"
399            )
400
401        raw_converted: list[CoordTup | str] = self.strings_to_coords(
402            self.token_arr, when_noncoord="include"
403        )
404
405        # filter out non-coordinates
406        return {
407            coord: i
408            for i, coord in enumerate(raw_converted)
409            if not isinstance(coord, str)
410        }
411
412    @cached_property
413    def coordinate_tokens_ids(self) -> dict[str, int]:
414        # checks performed in call
415        output: dict[str, int] = dict()
416
417        for coord, index in self.coordinate_tokens_coords.items():
418            _for_key: list[str] = self.coords_to_strings([coord])
419            assert len(_for_key) == 1
420            output[_for_key[0]] = index
421
422        return output
423
424    # other
425    # ============================================================
426
427    def summary(self) -> dict:
428        """returns a summary of the tokenization mode"""
429        return {
430            "tokenization_mode": self.tokenization_mode.value,
431            "max_grid_size": self.max_grid_size,
432            "vocab_size": self.vocab_size,
433        }
434
435    def is_AOTP(self) -> bool:
436        """returns true if a tokenization mode is Adjacency list, Origin, Target, Path"""
437        return self.tokenization_mode in (
438            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
439            TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
440            TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed,
441        )
442
443    def is_UT(self) -> bool:
444        return is_UT(self.tokenization_mode)
445
446    def clear_cache(self):
447        """clears all cached properties"""
448        # delete the properties only if they exist
449        for name, prop in self.__class__.__dict__.items():
450            if isinstance(prop, cached_property):
451                # if the property exists, delete it
452                try:
453                    delattr(self, name)
454                except AttributeError as e:
455                    pass

LEGACY Tokenizer for mazes

Caution

MazeTokenizerModular is the new standard for tokenization. This class is no longer recommended for use, but will remain for compatibility with existing code.

Parameters:

  • tokenization_mode: TokenizationMode mode of tokenization. required.
    • max_grid_size: int | None maximum grid size. required for actually turning text tokens to numerical tokens, but not for moving between coordinates/mazes and text

Properties

  • name: str auto-generated name of the tokenizer from mode and size

Conditional Properties

  • node_strings_map: Mapping[CoordTup, str] map from node to string. This returns a muutils.kappa.Kappa object which you can use like a dictionary. returns None if not a UT mode

these all return None if max_grid_size is None. Prepend _ to the name to get a guaranteed type, and cause an exception if max_grid_size is None

  • token_arr: list[str] list of tokens, in order of their indices in the vocabulary
  • tokenizer_map: Mapping[str, int] map from token to index
  • vocab_size: int size of the vocabulary
  • padding_token_index: int index of the padding token

Methods

  • coords_to_strings(coords: list[CoordTup]) -> list[str] convert a list of coordinates to a list of tokens. Optionally except, skip, or ignore non-coordinates
  • strings_to_coords(strings: list[str]) -> list[CoordTup] convert a list of tokens to a list of coordinates. Optionally except, skip, or ignore non-coordinates

clears all cached properties

def serialize(self) -> dict[str, typing.Any]:
View on GitHub 
660        def serialize(self) -> dict[str, Any]:
661            result: dict[str, Any] = {
662                "__format__": f"{self.__class__.__name__}(SerializableDataclass)"
663            }
664            # for each field in the class
665            for field in dataclasses.fields(self):  # type: ignore[arg-type]
666                # need it to be our special SerializableField
667                if not isinstance(field, SerializableField):
668                    raise NotSerializableFieldException(
669                        f"Field '{field.name}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__} is not a `SerializableField`, "
670                        f"but a {type(field)} "
671                        "this state should be inaccessible, please report this bug!"
672                    )
673
674                # try to save it
675                if field.serialize:
676                    try:
677                        # get the val
678                        value = getattr(self, field.name)
679                        # if it is a serializable dataclass, serialize it
680                        if isinstance(value, SerializableDataclass):
681                            value = value.serialize()
682                        # if the value has a serialization function, use that
683                        if hasattr(value, "serialize") and callable(value.serialize):
684                            value = value.serialize()
685                        # if the field has a serialization function, use that
686                        # it would be nice to be able to override a class's `.serialize()`, but that could lead to some inconsistencies!
687                        elif field.serialization_fn:
688                            value = field.serialization_fn(value)
689
690                        # store the value in the result
691                        result[field.name] = value
692                    except Exception as e:
693                        raise FieldSerializationError(
694                            "\n".join(
695                                [
696                                    f"Error serializing field '{field.name}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__}",
697                                    f"{field = }",
698                                    f"{value = }",
699                                    f"{self = }",
700                                ]
701                            )
702                        ) from e
703
704            # store each property if we can get it
705            for prop in self._properties_to_serialize:
706                if hasattr(cls, prop):
707                    value = getattr(self, prop)
708                    result[prop] = value
709                else:
710                    raise AttributeError(
711                        f"Cannot serialize property '{prop}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__}"
712                        + f"but it is in {self._properties_to_serialize = }"
713                        + f"\n{self = }"
714                    )
715
716            return result

@classmethod
def load(cls, data: Union[dict[str, Any], ~T]) -> Type[~T]:
View on GitHub 
723        @classmethod  # type: ignore[misc]
724        def load(cls, data: dict[str, Any] | T) -> Type[T]:
725            # HACK: this is kind of ugly, but it fixes a lot of issues for when we do recursive loading with ZANJ
726            if isinstance(data, cls):
727                return data
728
729            assert isinstance(
730                data, typing.Mapping
731            ), f"When loading {cls.__name__ = } expected a Mapping, but got {type(data) = }:\n{data = }"
732
733            cls_type_hints: dict[str, Any] = get_cls_type_hints(cls)
734
735            # initialize dict for keeping what we will pass to the constructor
736            ctor_kwargs: dict[str, Any] = dict()
737
738            # iterate over the fields of the class
739            for field in dataclasses.fields(cls):
740                # check if the field is a SerializableField
741                assert isinstance(
742                    field, SerializableField
743                ), f"Field '{field.name}' on class {cls.__name__} is not a SerializableField, but a {type(field)}. this state should be inaccessible, please report this bug!\nhttps://github.com/mivanit/muutils/issues/new"
744
745                # check if the field is in the data and if it should be initialized
746                if (field.name in data) and field.init:
747                    # get the value, we will be processing it
748                    value: Any = data[field.name]
749
750                    # get the type hint for the field
751                    field_type_hint: Any = cls_type_hints.get(field.name, None)
752
753                    # we rely on the init of `SerializableField` to check that only one of `loading_fn` and `deserialize_fn` is set
754                    if field.deserialize_fn:
755                        # if it has a deserialization function, use that
756                        value = field.deserialize_fn(value)
757                    elif field.loading_fn:
758                        # if it has a loading function, use that
759                        value = field.loading_fn(data)
760                    elif (
761                        field_type_hint is not None
762                        and hasattr(field_type_hint, "load")
763                        and callable(field_type_hint.load)
764                    ):
765                        # if no loading function but has a type hint with a load method, use that
766                        if isinstance(value, dict):
767                            value = field_type_hint.load(value)
768                        else:
769                            raise FieldLoadingError(
770                                f"Cannot load value into {field_type_hint}, expected {type(value) = } to be a dict\n{value = }"
771                            )
772                    else:
773                        # assume no loading needs to happen, keep `value` as-is
774                        pass
775
776                    # store the value in the constructor kwargs
777                    ctor_kwargs[field.name] = value
778
779            # create a new instance of the class with the constructor kwargs
780            output: cls = cls(**ctor_kwargs)
781
782            # validate the types of the fields if needed
783            if on_typecheck_mismatch != ErrorMode.IGNORE:
784                output.validate_fields_types(on_typecheck_error=on_typecheck_error)
785
786            # return the new instance
787            return output

takes in an appropriately structured dict and returns an instance of the class, implemented by using @serializable_dataclass decorator
